President Biden has signed a Presidential Memorandum highlighting the administration's commitment to worker rights globally. The memorandum directs federal departments and agencies to promote labor rights and worker empowerment in their international efforts. President Biden aims to establish high labor standards, include workers' voices in decision-making, and enforce rules against unfair labor practices worldwide. The memorandum emphasizes the importance of common standards and fundamental rights to ensure fair competition in the global economy. Additionally, it recognizes the role of workers and labor organizations in defending democracy. The memorandum builds upon previous actions, such as the establishment of the White House Task Force on Worker Organizing and Empowerment and partnerships with international leaders like Brazilian President Lula da Silva. The administration plans to collaborate with partners, allies, labor unions, and international organizations to achieve these goals.